    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Adding a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gksknodecomponent"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object to an entity automatically updates the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sknode/1640688-entity"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property of the componentâ€™s SpriteKit node (an "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sknode"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object) to point to that entity."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When you add entities and components to a node in the Xcode SpriteKit scene editor, Xcode automatically creates a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gksknodecomponent"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object to manage the relationship between that SpriteKit node and the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkentity"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object that node represents. Load the scene file with the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkscene"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " class to access these entities and components."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": false,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gksknodecomponent"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " class adopts the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkagentdelegate"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " protocol. If you use the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkagent2d"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " class to drive the movement of game entities, set your "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": false,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gksknodecomponent"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " instance as the delegate for the entityâ€™s agent, and GameplayKit will automatically synchronize the agent and its SpriteKit representation."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "note",
          "name": "Tip"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For more information on Entity-Component architecture, read "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": "Entities and Components",
              "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/General/Conceptual/GameplayKit_Guide/EntityComponent.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40015172-CH6"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " in "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": "GameplayKit Programming Guide",
              "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/General/Conceptual/GameplayKit_Guide/index.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40015172"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        }
